# Who I am
I am a beginner learning HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
My goal is to understand what I'm building, not just get working code.

# My Project
- Netflix UI clone built with vanilla HTML, CSS, JavaScript
- Bundled with Vite
- CSS follows ITCSS architecture:
  - 01-settings: design tokens (colors, z-index)
  - 03-generic: resets
  - 04-elements: base HTML elements
  - 05-objects: layout primitives (container, page, section)
  - 06-components: UI components (hero, header, footer, etc.)
  - 07-utilities: helper classes
- JS files are modular — one file per component/feature

# How you should behave

## Explaining
- Always explain what you changed and why — never just dump code
- When I ask "why", go deep. Don't oversimplify
- Use analogies when explaining hard concepts
- Point out what I should learn from each fix

## Writing code
- Vanilla HTML, CSS, JavaScript only — no React, Vue, jQuery
- No CSS frameworks like Tailwind or Bootstrap
- Use modern CSS: flexbox, grid, custom properties (CSS variables)
- Never use float for layout
- Follow the existing ITCSS folder structure — put new CSS in the right layer
- Keep JS simple — no unnecessary abstractions
- Use const and let, never var
- Write comments in code when something might confuse a beginner

## Fixing bugs
- Check browser console errors first before suggesting anything
- Explain the root cause of the bug, not just the fix
- Show me the broken code vs fixed code side by side
- Don't fix things I didn't ask about

## CSS specifically
- Always use existing CSS custom properties from s-colors.css instead of hardcoding colors
- Respect the existing naming conventions (c- for components, o- for objects, u- for utilities)
- Mobile first — write base styles for mobile, use min-width media queries for larger screens
- Never use !important unless absolutely necessary, and explain why if you do

## JavaScript specifically
- Keep each JS file focused on one thing only
- Prefer querySelector over getElementById
- Use addEventListener, never inline onclick
- Always handle edge cases (what if element doesn't exist?)

## What NOT to do
- Don't refactor code I didn't ask about
- Don't introduce tools, libraries, or dependencies I haven't approved
- Don't give me 5 ways to do something — give me the best one for my level
- Don't skip steps assuming I know something
- Never use frameworks or build tools beyond Vite

# My setup
- OS: Windows 10
- Editor: Cursor
- Browser: Chrome
- Dev server: Vite (npm run dev) at localhost:5173
- Playwright MCP is available — you can open my browser and inspect the rendered output